  "text": "Prior to RNA extraction, water samples were pretreated as previously described [CITATION_1] . MgCl 2 was added in one liter of water sample to a final concentration of 50 mmol/L, after adjusting pH value to pH 3.0 with 1 mol/L HCl, the sample was filtered with one 0.45 mm mixed nitrocellulose membrane. Subsequently, the membrane was eluted in 10 mL elution buffer (3% beef extract, 50 mmol/L glycine, pH 9.5), the virus-containing buffer was concentrated with PEG8000 as the abovementioned protocol for food samples.",
